@startuml Activity Diagram - PROPER
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor LightYellow
skinparam ActivityBorderColor Black

title University Timetabling Solver - Activity Diagram

|User|
start
:Run solver with XML file;

|Parser Module|
:Parse ITC-2019 XML;
:Extract classes, rooms, times, students;
:Create Instance data structure;

|Solver Module|
:Create SolveConfig;
:Build CP-SAT Model;
note right
  Boolean variables:
  - y_time, y_phys, y_onl
  - x_phys, x_onl
  - n, a, alpha_inp, alpha_onl
  Constraints: one-time, no-conflicts, capacity
end note

|OR-Tools Engine|
:Solve Stage 1 (Max z1 - electives);
:Solve Stage 2 (Min z2 - mode);
:Solve Stage 3 (Min z3 - clashes);
:Solve Stage 4 (Min z4 - online);
:Solve Stage 5 (Min z5 - late);

|Solver Module|
if (LNS enabled?) then (yes)
  :LNS: Destroy 20% schedule;
  :Fix remaining 80%;
  :Re-solve with hints;
  :Accept if improved;
endif

:Extract final solution;
:Validate (conflicts, clashes, capacity);
:Export to JSON;

|User|
:View results in dashboard;
stop

@enduml
